stories.storyText:
[Code Name] Surtr
[Gender] Female
[Combat Experience] 2 Years
[Place of Birth] Unknown
[Date of Birth] Jan 22
[Race] Sarkaz
[Height] 162cm
[Infection Status] 
Confirmed Infected by medical examination.

[Physical Strength] Normal
[Mobility] Normal
[Physical Resilience] Normal
[Tactical Acumen] Excellent
[Combat Skill] Normal
[Originium Arts Assimilation] Flawed

Surtr is a mysterious Sarkaz girl who suffers from amnesia, perhaps due to her Oripathy. Her condition is rarely seen even among Infected. She is currently undergoing treatment at Rhodes Island. 
During testing, Surtr displayed an inexplicably high combat prowess, and was quickly drafted as a combat operator.

Imaging tests have shown the outlines of her internal organs to be indistinct due to slight shadows. Minute amounts of Originium granules have been detected in her circulatory system, confirming her to be infected with Oripathy. 

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 1%
Operator Surtr has basically no signs of infection on the surface of her body. 

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] 0.10u/L
Operator Surtr's Originium-Crystal density is at the lower end.

Operator Surtr was found in the ruins of a small town ravaged by a Catastrophe, on the outskirts of Ursus. At the time, Rhodes Island operators were carrying out a post-Catastrophe scouting mission and stumbled upon Surtr, who was resting alone in a destroyed building. Assuming that Surtr was a victim of the Catastrophe and afraid that she would fall victim to its aftereffects, the operators decided to bring her back to Rhodes Island. It was only later that we realized Surtr was merely a passing traveler looking for a place to rest.

Though Surtr's combat prowess far surpasses the average combat operator, her power cannot be attributed to any kind of Originium Arts. With the two-handed sword she carries, Surtr can do significant damage to her environs. The sheer heat emitted from the blade can melt most substances, but the theory behind it is difficult to explain. Surtr herself is unable to recall the origin of the sword. It became an indispensable companion without her noticing. Because of this, even if Surtr frequently passes through normal Infected areas, her Infection will not significantly worsen. Whether it will become a key area of interest in the research of Oripathy remains unknown at this point.

Surtr's memory impairment is different from normal amnesia, and is more akin to memory confusion due to overlapping memories within the same period of time. Based on Surtr's explanation, her mind contains many differing memories. In these memories, Surtr herself could be in completely different locations, with completely different interpersonal relationships. Due to the difficulty of investigation, the authenticity of her report cannot be determined as of now. It is unconfirmed if these are really Surtr's own experiences, or others' experiences that Surtr came to treat as her own.

Surtr's lifestyle on the Rhodes Island landship is rather free, without many of the constraints and requirements expected of normal operators. Medical understands her circumstances, and has compiled a partial list of Surtr's memories to aid in her investigation. Surtr spends most of her time looking for clues at the locations in her memories. It is clear that Surtr may never be able to finish investigating all the locations in her memories within her lifetime, but Surtr herself does not seem to mind. Perhaps to her, the journey is far more important than the destination.

[A particular page of Surtr's personal records]
[No permission required for viewing]
Forest, endless trees, stream, carriage, bandits. 
Skyscrapers, alleyway, cake shop, icing, albumen. 
Wasteland, ruins, enemies, friends, a series of explosions. 
Snowy mountain, a barren snowy mountain, unending snowy mountains. 
Castle, stone castle, tower, unopenable door. 
School, street, sports field, newsstand, mugger. 
Police station, interrogation room, timer, criminal. 
Balloons, amusement park, fountain, roller coaster. 
Ocean, sea monster, fishing boats. 
Electric tower, broadcast station, rooftop. 
————
Many lines have been crossed out.

modules.desc:
Operator Surtr has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude for inflicting Arts damage on the enemy in close-quarters combat.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Guard Operator during field operations to exercise Arts Fighter responsibilities.
In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named.

'Sami blesses and protects us all. It is everywhere, and ever watchful over Its children.
'Every tree, every blade of grass in this tundra is part of It, and through them It guides us. Even in distant lands, It reaches through these mediums to aid us in troubled times.
'So what do you say? A handcrafted Sami spirit stone? Even the great Arges bought one, you know.' —A certain incorrigible Sami peddler
As Surtr, amidst the heart of the blizzard, prepared to leave the icefields' depths, Sami gave her a gift.
Slowly, the sheaves of frozen runes revealed to her melted, crumbled, and a stone of crystal ice fell at her feet.
As if compelled, Surtr picked it up, and found it not nearly as bone-chilling as its looks suggested. Even as the blizzard bathed it, it pulsed with a warmer rhythm. Almost a familiar one. The rhythm of life.
Such a familiar feeling. She looked at the sword in her hand, staring at the molten core within it.
Bringing the crystal to her sword, Surtr could feel... another self stirring, a voice crying out, 'Damn you, take that thing away! Get it out of my sight!'
So, Surtr bought one of those locally handcrafted Sami pendants, discarded its useless rock, and replaced it with the crystal. She wound the rope around the sword's hilt.
With every step forward, the pendant and hilt would knock together in rhythm—clank, clank. This annoyed her other self greatly, haughty yet powerless to resist.
In the back of her mind, Surtr couldn't help but laugh at it.
She knew it was a seething, scorching sort, easy to irritate, hated cold things the way one might hate the sound of nails on a chalkboard.
It was why she'd always loved ice cream, and all cold refreshments alike.
Clank, clank—Surtr knocked the pendant on the blade a few times, and it gave a few violent shakes in response, before settling down once more. The crystal's blue light bathed the blade's flame red, smothering it somewhat.
Thank you, Sami.
She could feel its blaze becoming wrath, increasingly unable to bear being slighted so, as if saying, 'You fool! You would choose this most pathetic, most damnable of means to get back at me!'
Nonsense.
She'd never considered its minor griping a threat, with or without Sami's help.
She's never seen her fiery powers as a blessing, nor has she ever felt restricted by the chaos that is her memory. Headstrong and self-centered, she disregards and cherishes as she sees fit.
Feranmut fragment? Big deal. Just shut it in front of me.

voice_lines.voiceText: You couldn't even finish the work you're supposed to do, so you're asking me for help?
Stop sending me to teach people Originium Arts. I have no interest in wasting time with common people.
I'm not here because I have to be. Just because I want to be.
The people I hate most are the ones who ask too many questions. I hope you are not one of them.
Looks like you understand my Arts now, to some degree. I hope you're aware of the danger as well.
Before I realized it, these Arts and this staff became my most loyal friends. I don't remember when I gained this power. And of course, I don't actually care.

I have all kinds of memories. I don't know where they came from, and I don't know which ones are really mine. I've been traveling back and forth, from country to country trying to find the source. And now, here I am at Rhodes Island.
When I'm all caught up in chaotic memories, there's nothing better than an ice cream to calm me down. I relied a lot on ice cream, when I was alone.

The memories from after I came to Rhodes Island are completely different from the ones before. There's a sense of realism to them. For the first time, I feel like I'm really myself. That's all thanks to you, and the rest of Rhodes Island… What? I am capable of giving thanks where it's deserved, alright?
Hmph… what a waste of time.
I am Surtr. Are you the Doctor they mentioned? I'll be working at Rhodes Island, starting today. I hope you won't bore me too much.
That's it?
What? You're starting to value me now that you know my power?
So it's not my power, but me myself? Hmph, you leave me no choice but to pay it back with hard work.
Am I needed?
I alone am enough.
Time to go.
Are they the ones I'm eliminating?
Don't order me around.
Enough, I get it.
Not a bad position.
I'm on it!
Die!
You can run but you can't hide!
Laevatain!
Foolish morons!
Hmph. Piece of cake.
Naturally.
Can you not even do such a simple thing?
If you can't help, just run! I'll handle this.
This room is clean enough, I guess.
I can find my own way.
Quiet, please.
Arknights.

This day has always irritated me a little. Time goes by one year after another, and my memories also drift further and further away... Hmph, forget it. Hey you, come take a stroll with me on the deck. Maybe some cold wind will help calm me down.
Oh, here you are.

Happy birthday. You remember your birthday, even though you're amnesiac. That has to mean that something really important must've happened on this day… Um, I have your birthday memorized now, and I won't forget it this time.

For now, I still don't have a way to find my past self, but the process has also shaped who I am today. My days here at Rhodes Island are an important part of that. Doctor, we still have a lot of time together ahead of us. Keep your faith in my sword.
